cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is about face attribute editing using deep convolutional networks and generative adversarial networks. The main focus is on improving the capability of editing multiple attributes by exemplars and enhancing the quality of the generated image. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of attribute classification loss and a novel model structure, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of generative models and image manipulation techniques could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.GR (Graphics).
